The food here is delicious. Love their cauliflower appetizer and pretty much any pizza you order is fantastic. However, I really hate the general experience dining there. The valet is super expensive, the dining room is cramped and very noisy, and in the summer it's sweltering inside. Their AC unit just can't seem to compete with the ovens going all day in back. Also, our group wanted to order a bottle each of red and white wine and, when we asked our waiter for his recommendation, he easily pointed to the most expensive bottle of each. Really? I highly doubt that would be his genuine preference if he were to order himself.

Horrible delivery service. If I was able to put 0/5 I would for many reasons. One being the lack of training for employees to treat consumers the right way. I called around 10:15 pm today, July 4th. I order a large meats pizza and garlic Parmesan breadsticks for delivery and the guy that took my order was not having the best attitude. He did not take the time to repeat my address nor my phone number, it sounded as if he was in a rush and I understand because it was a holiday and I’m guessing they had many orders but maybe they should consider hiring someone that can handle the job. Not only that but I waited more than 2 HOURS for those items to arrive. The first time I called I was told that they had taken the wrong phone number and so the delivery guy had to go back but that they were going to send him back. Time went by and there was no sign of my order so I called AGAIN to see what was going on and I was told that the driver was a couple minutes away. 45 minutes had passed and at this point I was ready to cancel the order but the driver arrived. And as I thought, the food was already cold, and of course after 2 hours how was it supposed to be warm even with the heater they say they use. This is the second time I order and on my previous order I also experienced some issues for sending my order earlier than what I had scheduled it on Grubhub. At this point I learned my lesson and I won’t be ordering again.
